{"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Configuring your user’s device ID with "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Customize Behavior","generated":true,"anchor":"Customize-Behavior","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/BrazeDelegate","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/overrideResourceBundle"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"BrazeKit"},{"type":"text","text":", a user can be identified using one of two device ID options:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uidevice\/1620059-identifierforvendor","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" property."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A randomly generated UUID."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because "},{"code":"identifierForVendor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" may not be available in all scenarios or devices, Braze provides the option to use a more generic UUID to identify a user’s device."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Setting-Your-Configuration","text":"Setting Your Configuration","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To configure this option, set ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" under ","type":"text"},{"code":"Braze.Configuration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Assigning this property to ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will generate a random UUID for each user installation, whereas a value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will notify the SDK to use the device’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"identifierForVendor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let configuration = Braze.Configuration(","    apiKey: \"<BRAZE_API_KEY>\",","    endpoint: \"<BRAZE_ENDPOINT>\"",")","\/\/ Set this value to `true` to opt out of `identifierForVendor` usage.","configuration.useUUIDAsDeviceId = true","let braze = Braze(configuration: configuration)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Starting in 7.0.0, the default value for this property is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For device types that do not support "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifierForVendor"},{"type":"text","text":", such as watchOS or macOS, Braze will default to a randomly generated UUID regardless of which option is configured."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After being generated, device IDs created from UUIDs will remain consistent throughout the lifetime of the application’s installation or until "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/wipeData()"},{"type":"text","text":" is called."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/wipeData()"},{"text":" will erase all local SDK storage, the device ID that was previously stored will be deleted. Thus, if ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId"},{"text":" is enabled, the SDK will generate a new UUID for the device ID after this operation. Similarly, if ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId"},{"text":" is disabled, the SDK will re-use the same IDFV after this operation.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Important"},{"anchor":"Migrating-from-a-Previous-Version","text":"Migrating from a Previous Version","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are migrating your project from the legacy "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Appboy\/appboy-ios-sdk"},{"type":"text","text":" or from a version of the Braze Swift SDK prior to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"5.7.0"},{"type":"text","text":", note that the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifierForVendor"},{"type":"text","text":" option will be used by default, regardless of the configuration setting. This ensures continuity for any anonymous users previously identified by the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifierForVendor"},{"type":"text","text":" device ID."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In such cases, if you wish to override those pre-existing values and ensure that your "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" configuration is respected, call "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/wipeData()","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Braze"},{"type":"text","text":" instance after migrating to any version of the Braze Swift SDK from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"5.7.0"},{"type":"text","text":" onwards."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/Braze\/device-id-configuration"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"BrazeKit"}],"title":"Device ID Configuration","role":"article"},"references":{"doc://Braze/documentation/BrazeKit/Braze":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Braze"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze"},{"text":" is the main entry point of the BrazeKit module and provides access to all its features.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/brazekit\/braze","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Braze"}],"title":"Braze"},"doc://Braze/documentation/BrazeKit/Braze/Configuration-swift.class":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Configuration"}],"url":"\/documentation\/brazekit\/braze\/configuration-swift.class","title":"Braze.Configuration","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Braze SDK configuration."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Configuration"}]},"doc://Braze/documentation/BrazeKit/Braze/Configuration-swift.class/useUUIDAsDeviceId":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Determines if a randomly generated UUID should be used as the device ID"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId","title":"useUUIDAsDeviceId","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"ident